    <h1 class="c-heading c-heading--lg">Accessibility Statement</h1>

    <div class="c-article__body">

      <h2>Commitment</h2>
      <p>I'm committed to making this site accessible to everyone, regardless of ability or technology. As someone who leads accessibility efforts for New York State, I take this responsibility seriously — not just professionally, but personally.</p>

      <h2>Standards</h2>
      <p>This site aims to conform to the <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2</a> at Level AA. These guidelines explain how to make web content more accessible to people with disabilities.</p>

      <h2>Testing</h2>
      <p>I regularly test this site using a combination of:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Automated testing tools (axe, Lighthouse)</li>
        <li>Manual keyboard navigation testing</li>
        <li>Screen reader testing (VoiceOver on macOS)</li>
        <li>Browser zoom and text scaling</li>
        <li>Reduced motion and high contrast mode testing</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Known Issues</h2>
      <p>There are no known accessibility issues at this time. If you encounter any, please let me know.</p>

      <h2>Report an Issue</h2>
      <p>If you experience any difficulty accessing content on this site, please reach out. I want to hear from you and will do my best to address the issue promptly.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:jesse@plasticmind.com">jesse@plasticmind.com</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Last Reviewed</h2>
      <p>This statement was last reviewed on February 28, 2026.</p>

    </div>

